			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2383411">
									

<p>You could write a long and epic and sprawling tale and include a three-word throwaway where someone burned 012 to ashes, just out of spite, and 012 would probably still gain votes. It'll be one of those skips that continues to gain votes no matter what happens.</p>
<p>I think re-contextualizing a (from the POV of the person writing the tale) shitty skip and turning it into something better isn't a bad thing. In fact, people have done that with stuff like 343, 105, 076, 049, 106, 682, 173, 2000, etc. etc., even the goddamn Jester. I think being doubtful that a tale based off a skip you don't like is valid, but to say that writing about it is fruitless seems defeatist to me.</p>

							</div>

								
					
