					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183131" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;" >WrongJohnSilver</a></span> <span class="odate time_1443538673 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Sep 2015 14:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2383572">
									

<p>Thank you for the upvote, MacLeod. I'm quite aware of your dislike of the 012 article (and I share yours and Kalinin's opinion&#8212;it's a bad article). I fully expected a downvote from you for that reason. So, getting an upvote from you means a lot to me.</p>
<p>But yes, as Decibelle said, I don't think I've done anything to keep 012 around. It's over +100. It's in Containment Breach. Believe me, if I could rewrite it, I totally would. Furthermore, I know that if it descended to the negatives, it would be rewritten, if not by me then by someone. It would not be simply deleted. 012 will stay, whatever my efforts are or not.</p>
<p>012 is in such a strange space. The article is spotty and poorly constructed. It can be simplified to something what crazies you to death. However, there's a core, a soul to the article that is compelling. I want to explore it. I'm driven to deconstruct the barebones structure and infuse the life within it that we can see <em>should</em> be there.</p>
<p>The 012 article is kind of like 012 itself.</p>

							</div>

								
					
