    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2383566">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2383566">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2383566)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2383566">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183131" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;" >WrongJohnSilver</a></span> <span class="odate time_1443537814 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Sep 2015 14:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2383566">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Staying with me in my room are two other Americans, Anderson and Spitzer. They arrived together, and work together back in the States. They say that they're going to clear out the National Library, see what texts can be salvaged.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Spitzer's also a Foundation agent. Anderson's earlier statement about Spitzer being exposed to the quarto was further evidence of their relationship. Yes, I'm writing without directly linking to <a href="/scp-701">SCP-701</a>, but the implied backstory is that Anderson and Spitzer are in Florence to recover a 1640 quarto of SCP-701. The flood is just the opportunity.</p>
<p>&quot;All the best&quot;: &#8230;That should have been &quot;All for the best.&quot; Will fix.</p>
<p>And yes, 7/12 time (which is actually <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_signature#Irrational_meters" target="_blank">a thing</a>, in short bits) is deliberate. Partly because 012 is a &quot;disagreeable cacophony,&quot; and partly because there's an in-world Easter egg there. (Also, I can write copious amounts of insane numerology.)</p>
<p>I'll review the events of 14 and 15, make sure it's clear enough what's going on.</p>
<p>I'm not good with colors, though. I was hoping for a darker red, but didn't know how to make it.</p>
<p>But all in all, I'm just glad that I could take this line:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-012 was retrieved by Archaeologist K.M. Sandoval during the excavation of a northern Italian tomb destroyed in a recent storm.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>and connect it to important real-life events. It also was the great source of the photos (photos of the aftermath of the 1966 Florence flood are public domain from the Italian government, the photo of the 1966 Leonids is from NASA, and the music is from Beethoven's notes).</p>

							</div>

								
					
